Change has been successfully rebased and submitted as 720c989829920ac5b6837280e9b4b53815b01895

This code will never build, because it was split up into 4 reviews to make it easier to review.  The end result of the generated files is essentially the same when we're done, but the intermediate changes would necessitate a difficult review.

I would expect this whole series to merge at the same time, and be tested on the last commit.

For whatever reason the old code was pulling from the Json schemas for this, not the CSDL.  For this file, CSDL is what it should've been doing, hence this change, but this change doesn't effect anything, because no redfish instance should be producing these schemas.
So "using" a schema will be adding the symlink? And no rerunning of update_schemas. ack.
for now you still need to rerun to rebuild metadata.xml, but that fix is next.
